# ==============================================================================
# FILE        : database-services.conf.example
# ==============================================================================
# Synopsis    : Example batch listener configuration — common database ports
# Description : One port per line. Lines starting with # are comments; blank
#               lines are ignored; invalid lines are skipped with a warning.
#               Inline comments are NOT supported: a port must be alone on its
#               line. Use with:
#               socat-manager batch --file database-services.conf.example
# Notes       : Listening on database ports is typically used to capture or
#               observe client connection attempts, not to serve a database.
# Version     : 1.0.1
# ==============================================================================

# MySQL / MariaDB
3306
# PostgreSQL
5432
# Redis
6379
# MongoDB
27017
# Microsoft SQL Server
1433
# Cassandra
9042
# CouchDB
5984
